## Tailwind CSS conventions

### Use CSS custom properties for semantic colors — never raw hex in className

```tsx
// ✓ semantic tokens
<div className="bg-background text-foreground border-border" />
<p className="text-muted-foreground" />
<span className="text-primary bg-accent" />
<button className="text-destructive hover:bg-destructive/10" />

// ✗ hardcoded colors in app components
<div className="bg-white text-gray-900" />
```

**Exception**: The sidebar and header use intentional gray-900 for the dark chrome style:
```tsx
// Sidebar / Header — dark chrome, intentional
<aside className="bg-gray-900 text-white border-gray-700" />
```

### Available CSS custom properties (defined in index.css)

```
--background / --foreground
--primary / --primary-foreground
--secondary / --secondary-foreground
--muted / --muted-foreground
--accent / --accent-foreground
--destructive / --destructive-foreground
--border / --input / --ring / --radius
--header-height: 3.5rem
--sidebar-width: 15rem
--sidebar-width-collapsed: 3.75rem
```

### `cn()` — always use for conditional classes

```tsx
// ✓
className={cn(
  "flex items-center rounded-md px-3 py-2 text-sm",
  isActive && "bg-accent text-primary font-medium",
  disabled && "opacity-50 pointer-events-none",
)}

// ✗ string concatenation
className={"flex " + (isActive ? "bg-accent" : "")}
```

